# Smoke data humanizer（EN / KM）

When writing **smoke tests**, **seed payloads**, **Playwright fills**, **PAI probes**, or **evidence remarks** that land in shared/dev DB (boss may open screens):

## Do

1. Use **natural insurance wording** — reads like underwriter / ops typed it.
2. Always fill **EN + KM** when the form/API has both (`*_kh`, KH Accept-Language, dual labels).
3. **Vary** strings per run (date fragment, site, small random noun) — avoid copy-paste identical remarks every smoke.
4. Keep short: 1 sentence EN, 1 short KM clause. No essays.
5. Prefer realistic options: CUSTOM endorsement types, inventory/location/sum-insured reasons, polite reject remarks.

## Don’t (boss complain list)

| Bad | Why |
|-----|-----|
| `smoke`, `test`, `asdf`, `xxx`, `12345` | Looks like QA junk |
| `UI smoke reject 2026-07-22` | Agent fingerprint |
| `lorem ipsum`, `foo/bar/baz` | Non-business |
| Same string EN copied into KM | Looks lazy / broken i18n |
| ALL CAPS spam / emoji | Unprofessional on schedule/PDF |

## Good examples (rotate)

**Endorsement type EN:** `Increase Sum Insured — Warehouse Stock`  
**Type KM:** `បង្កើនទឹកប្រាក់ធានា — ទំនិញក្នុងឃ្លាំង`

**Description EN:** `Mid-term change: add stock coverage at Battambang warehouse per insured request.`  
**Description KM:** `កែប្រែពាក់កណ្តាលរយៈពេល៖ បន្ថែមការធានាទំនិញនៅឃ្លាំងបាត់ដំបងតាមសំណើអ្នកធានា។`

**Reject remark EN:** `Supporting schedule incomplete — please reattach the inventory list.`  
**Reject remark KM:** `តារាងភ្ជាប់មិនគ្រប់គ្រាន់ — សូមភ្ជាប់បញ្ជីទំនិញឡើងវិញ។`

**Approve remark EN:** `Within authority — documents reviewed.`  
(empty OK if API allows)

## Where it applies

- `scripts/smoke-*.mjs` / `scripts/smoke-*.php`
- Manual PAI/Laravel smoke bodies
- Evidence query text that quotes payload values (can note “humanized”)
- Any FE default placeholder written into persistent records

## Coexistence

- Caveman replies stay short; **payload strings** still human.
- Does not replace PL seven-product scope or verification rules.
